<p>I am trying to make a element-builder (CMS) with which you can drag and drop elements into a page and easily create websites. I am using the bootstrap templates (css,js) to get a responsive website.</p>  <p>The problem is the following:</p>  <pre><code>_col-md-4_______________________ |                               | | Page Title                    | |_______________________________| |           |                   | |Image      | (main content)    | |           |                   | |           |                   | |div=col-xs-2___div=col-xs-10___| </code></pre>  <p>My title must be aligned above the main content.</p>  <p>I tried to create a responsive result by using Javascript:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;script&gt;$(document).ready(function() {     var witdh = $(\'.calculate-witdh\').innerWidth();     $(".title-offset").each(function(){$(this).css(\'margin-left\', witdh)});     });     $(window).resize(function() {     var witdh = $(\'.calculate-witdh\').innerWidth();     $(".title-offset").each(function(){$(this).css(\'margin-left\', witdh)});     });     &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But I think there has to be a better solution? Mainly because I don't want each element to load in it's own script.</p>  <p>Example found here: <a href="http://jsfiddle.net/abayob/vuskazh1/" rel="nofollow">http://jsfiddle.net/abayob/vuskazh1/</a></p>  <p>Any ideas?</p>